# Memory Discipline Rules

1. Treat `.cursor/memories/roadmap.md` as the single progress tracker.
2. When starting or switching major tasks, update current focus and module status in roadmap memory.
3. Treat `.cursor/memories/architecture.md` as the latest agreed architecture snapshot (target system shape).
4. Treat `.cursor/memories/architecture-decisions.md` as the architecture decision log (rationale and tradeoffs).
5. Keep the `Session Briefing` block in roadmap current and concise; this is the default context handoff.
6. Put unresolved reproducible blockers only in `.cursor/memories/debuglog.md`.
7. Put reusable lessons only in `.cursor/memories/memo.md`.
8. Treat `.cursor/memories/product-blueprint.md` as the canonical product definition (intent, UX behavior, staged delivery).
9. Avoid duplication across memory files; each fact should have one home and references elsewhere.
